On the shores of Shenzhen Bay lies Shenzhen City, a metropolis where large stretches of mangrove grow. The mangrove thrives on the wetlands between land and sea. In this transitional space, the trees form part of the unique ecosystem. Watch the video to see more. About 'Journeys in Nature': Southern Lingnan series Nanling Mountains stand in China's southern region. They divide the Yangtze River valley from the basin of the Pearl River. After eons of change and upheaval, Nanling embraces myriad mid-subtropical life-forms as their habitat and refuge. For more: Southern Lingnan series: Blue-throated Bee-eater Southern Lingnan series: Chinese Pangolin (Cover image via VCG) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)